text: Just wanted to pop in and say that the 12 commander damage thing has me winning on turn 3 almost every game with my joust deck. Not sure it's a great idea.

I think the bigger problem is its not you winning on t3. Its you killing a single player on t3. Maybe the other guys had defenses or whatever. Then on t4 they kill your guy with a fleshbag. Now the guy you killed just sits and watches
If the games are quick it doesn’t matter....:eyes:
40 :clap: card :clap: decks :clap: 15 :clap: life :clap:
My point is quick for 1 person isnt the same as quick for everyone
Exactly. So we should want to make it quick for everyone
It doesn’t matter if someone is knocked out turn three if everyone else is knocked out in 2-3 more turns
Fair enough. My only other critique there is that 12 is a clunky number.
Is there actual scoring in Jousting we could look up?
And that will somehow be less clunky?
There is actual scoring. I don’t know that it will translate though
Yeah, looking at it it doesn't seem like it would.

I think it’s 
3 for dismount 
2 for hit and broken lance
1 for a hit
Was just hoping the max score was 10 or something.
